  "texts": [
    "Breathing is not an action, it is rather a doing, something we do.",
    "A being is an agent if and only if can perform action [6].",
    "Furthermore, agency can be represented as an intentional system, to which one can ascribe beliefs and desires [7].",
    "This system may be a man, animal but not an isolated machine, because that requires a preprogrammed task by a human.",
    "Even the most intelligent machines nowadays are not capable of agency on their own accord; in the sense that without a commandment they do not perform actions."
